title: For Sale/Trade:  Romanian AES10-B RPK AK47 AK 47
postcontent: Up for bid is one outstanding Romanian made, AES10-B! This rifle is listed as used, however it is only listed that way because I bought it. It essentially has only had 10 rounds through it to test function. Let me give you a run down on this rifle. It has been professionally upgraded and straightened! Without getting into it about Century and it's wonderful work quality, I can absolutely guarantee this rifle is done right! For those who know, buying one of these rifles was a crap shoot at best! Sites came canted, mag wells came cut crooked, the incorrect bipods were installed, the wood furniture was unfinished, and the guns finish was terrible! These problems have all been addressed, and corrected on this rifle! To start, the correct Romanian heavy adjustable bipod has been installed! To do this, you must remove the front site to press the bipod collar onto the barrels chrome pad. To get around this, Century was installing the incorrect, quick release, non ajustible PKM bipod! They even welded shims onto the barrels chrome pad to do this! This is just poor workmanship. This rifle has the correct bipod that adjusts, cants the rifle left and right, and pivots it side to side! You can remove the cleaning rod, it properly locks into the front site, and you can stake the pads into the ground! The site alignment has been corrected and literally made, lazer straight!
